This was a big hit at Christmas dinner. However I did change it a bit. Since there were only four of us I only used the 2 pounds of potatoes (and no celery root) and then I used the full recipe for the spice mix and the liquid portion. Cooked the same amount of time.

Rating: 3
I loved this recipe and my guests said they did, too. However, my husband did not like the celery root. Next time, will make with just potatoes. I made it several hours ahead and refrigerated. (Did not discolor since sauce covered potatoes.) I added extra fontina with each of the layers. I think I cooked it a lot longer than the recipe said and it was for the best because it would have been runny if I didnt.

